  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThere are two main problems this issue should solve:\r\n\r\n1. Users can't mark notifications as `read` in a convenient way. For example, for mention notifications, they need to press on the notification, wait until the chat screen appears, go back to the AC and repeat the process N times.\r\n2. Users can't mark notifications as `unread`. Once the user performs an action on a notification, it's marked as read forever. This is not very helpful for users who want to use the AC to manage notifications.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nAllow the user to swipe right to toggle the `read` state. See the videos below and Figma for more details. If something is not clear, please, double-check with designers.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/214666397-ce3f6756-bbf3-4d1b-b488-ed7c9e3f95bc.mp4\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/214666531-6a786aa6-8a08-4976-9277-11421f1dd8fa.mp4\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n\r\nDon't implement the animations because they will probably change soon. Instead, we want to focus on the basic functionality first.\r\n\r\n### References\r\n\r\n`Figma - Shell for Mobile`: https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=5387%3A521771&t=ANqnR83VEKQqzHRY-0",
